{
  "texts": [
    "81) (default set to 100).",
    "For archetype a i, i ∈ 2,…, D, if it resides within a Euclidean distance of r from any archetype a j, j ∈ 1,…, i - 1, we merge a i with the closest a j.",
    "The archetypes distant from each other are kept after the shrinkage iteration and used in subsequent steps.",
    "We define archetypal communities as the r-nearest neighbors (same as the resolution parameter) to each archetype by constructing D clusters.",
    "Next, for each cluster i, we identify the top 30 marker genes by performing a Wilcoxon rank-sum test between in-group and out-of-group spots with Scanpy 82."
  ]
